The Southern Pyramid is the Moon Sovereign's counter-monument to the Solar Court.
Surface appearance is a modest funerary complex. The true structure descends through seven tiers consecrated to aspects of death.

The Moon Sovereign rejected the Solar Court's doctrine that sunlight was law made visible.
Instead declared true authority lay below, in underworld death forces. Each descending tier binds a death-function:
  Silence - suppression of dissent and witness control.
  Decay - managed ruin and reclamation from the dead.
  Shadow - surveillance through concealment.
  Bone - genealogy and legitimacy through remains.
  Venom - punishment refined to chemical efficiency.
  Fire - irreversible judgment and purification.
  Void - sovereign exception beyond all rite and law.

These seven aspects systematically invert the Solar Court's seven virtues of kingship.

The volcanic glass lake at the nadir was designed as a controlled interface with the anti-light source.
The Moon Sovereign believed the Black Sun Shard was a natural underworld emanation, not alien. Sought to learn its grammar rather than contain it.

The Eclipsed Tongues, the Moon Sovereign's faction, survived the sealing and merged with the Jackal Synod.
Modern Synod members who speak of "the eclipse that cleanses" unknowingly channel Moon Sovereign doctrine.
